text: Novoye Baryatino () is a rural locality (a selo) and the administrative center of Kazadayevsky Selsoviet, Sterlitamaksky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 613 as of 2010. There are 25 streets. == Geography == It is located 9 km from Sterlitamak. == References == Category:Rural localities in Sterlitamaksky District
title: Novoye Baryatino
